    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-29T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-29T19:00:00-05:00" n="399"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.8830/1785b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-29T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 29, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1298. Due to the critical shipping situation and in view of the fact that the
                    average monthly exports of newsprint to Argentina for the first 6 months of 1942
                    amounted to 4500 tons, the Department requests urgently the Embassy’s comments
                    as to whether 5000 tons per month would not be sufficient in view of the cut in
                    size of newspapers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
